<br>
I wrote a letter a long time ago to VI - this was pre-epic bs we are all used to, suggesting staged level dependant quests.<br>
<br>
Basically at level 1 you got a token from your GM (the ones you train at, not the guide staff) for turning in your note.<br>
<br>
Every level you could turn that coin back in and he would return it with a new one.<br>
<br>
Along the way you could &quot;purchase&quot; class specific nodrop items with these points accumulated. If you never spent a single token and at level 55 you had 55 points you could turn it in for something along the power of an epic.<br>
<br>
This required you to level, it required you to earn it in some fashion and it became a rite of passage type reward from your GM for being a good druid/cleric whatever.<br>
<br>
Why shouldnt every cleric at 55 be allowed to have an epic if they are in goodstanding in their guild? What does it do to the game but make it more enjoyable for its paying participants?<br>
<br>
Dont give me that crap about its not a right, not everyone should have one blah blah blah - epics are a dime a dozen, this is a game, you should be able to enjoy it without having to fight with fellow players on nonPvP servers. You want competition? Go race for 100s of other mobs in Norrath all day long if you want or go play Quake - or *gasp* move to a PvP server. I came to play a PvE game and I spend most of my time in a PvP world that just doesnt allow me to nuke the assholes.<br>
<br>
Of course Verant now uses my suggestion (no I am not taking credit for it I am sure there were plenty of other people with the same idea both internal and external to the company) on things like the shackle quests and many Cabilis quests. Its not a token system but they are progressive quests that dont have nearly the competition of things like Sevirilious and Ragefire.<br>
<br>
I want to earn my equipment too and I feel great pride when I have done so and have been successful in my adventures in Norrath. However, things like Ragefire totally take all that away and at 55+ it is almost essential to have multiple rez sticks in a guild. So it may not be &quot;required of all players to get their epic&quot; as Verants seems to think, but if you are 55+ and in a guild that raids at all... well it is pretty damn essential for the success of your friends on their travels.<br>
<br>
And yeah I know all about the memblur crap they use these days *sigh* this rotating GMs global queue is bad bad bad business for these types of deals. A permanent GM gets to know the players and the politics and in a case of guild vs guild they will tend to know who the liars and exploiters are over time, now they havent a clue. /rude VI CS <p><p align=left><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=81719>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide Tyrant<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br>"You must do the thing you think you cannot do." - Eleanor Roosevelt </font></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/27/02 9:22:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidonrufflefuzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidon Rufflefuzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Hobbit of Love</span><br>  Posts: 849<br> <font color=#333399>(6/27/02 10:12:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27712.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.engtong.com/Valoran/images/60x60/aidon60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lists do work</span><hr size=1> Do we have to kill Ragefire before or after we hand in the cleansed essence stuff to the Xanusus? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a target="new" href="http://w