<br>
The problems we're having now, though, are as more and more guilds become Ragefire-capable as the server matures, we're seeing our list get huge and cumbersome.  Some clerics have been waiting nearly a year to get their epics, which just isn't right.  I tried advocating a switch to a pure cleric-based rotation based on the date the cleric got their pearl, but guilds that preferred to wait until the last minute (ie, the night before their turn was up) to get their clerics Rage-ready didn't want to get burned by their laziness and wouldn't support it.  <br>
<br>
The best thing I've seen so far is a proposed move to a hybrid guild/cleric list with a maximum wait boundary multiplier based on the number of clerics currently on the list.  FCFS Ragefire is still bad juju on Torvonnilous, and we still firmly believe that the best way to give every cleric a fair shot at their epic is through a rotation or a list.<br>
<br>
Venril Sathir is still on a rotation, tho, holy cow, is that list HUGE.  o_O   <p><center><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/sithnferno/solro.jpg"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28741">Tyenu's Janx</a></center>
